## üõ†Ô∏è How to Run This Project

### 1. **Install Requirements**
- Java JDK 8 or above
- SQLite JDBC Driver (Download: [https://bit.ly/sqlite-jdbc](https://bit.ly/sqlite-jdbc))

### 2. **Clone the Repository**
```bash
git clone https://github.com/amulyakaleru07/JavaSwingUserManager

2. Import in Eclipse (or any IDE)
Open Eclipse ‚Üí File ‚Üí Import ‚Üí Existing Projects into Workspace

Select the cloned folder

Add the SQLite JDBC .jar file to your build path

3.Set up Database (Optional)
You can create a file like users.db and define a table like:
CREATE TABLE users (
    name TEXT,
    password TEXT,
    username TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    role TEXT
);

4.Run the Application
Run connection.java as a Java Application
The GUI will launch, and you can start using it


